# Supabase connection for the Expo app.
#
# These are read at build time by Expo. The EXPO_PUBLIC_ prefix is required so
# the values are inlined into the JS bundle and available via process.env.
# Copy this file to `apps/mobile/.env` and fill in the values for the target you
# are building against. `.env` is git-ignored — never commit real values.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LIVE / hosted Supabase (project: gujldqovvhjbctzelark)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This is what the published web build and the EAS native builds ship against.
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://gujldqovvhjbctzelark.supabase.co
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZSIsInJlZiI6Imd1amxkcW92dmhqYmN0emVsYXJrIiwicm9sZSI6ImFub24iLCJpYXQiOjE3ODA2NDA1MzAsImV4cCI6MjA5NjIxNjUzMH0.AlA5BiIjr741lqIIHhr241ZQ8cPhgwuVJV1aeNckzHg
#
# Get the URL + anon key from: Supabase Dashboard -> Project Settings -> API
# (the anon "public" key, or a modern `sb_publishable_...` key). The anon key is
# safe to embed in the client — RLS is what protects the data, not key secrecy.
#
# In CI / hosting, these are supplied as build-time env vars rather than a file:
#   * Vercel (web):  Project -> Settings -> Environment Variables
#   * EAS (native):  `eas.json` build profile `env`, or EAS project secrets
# See apps/mobile/README.md ("Environment variables") for details.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LOCAL development (Docker stack via `pnpm --filter @scrappd/supabase db:start`)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Copy the API URL + anon key printed by `db:start` (or run `supabase status`).
#
# IMPORTANT (physical device / Expo Go):
#   127.0.0.1 points at the phone itself, not your dev machine. Replace the host
#   with your computer's LAN IP (e.g. http://192.168.1.42:54321) so Expo Go on
#   the iPhone can reach the local Supabase stack.

EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54321
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZS1kZW1vIiwicm9sZSI6ImFub24iLCJleHAiOjE5ODM4MTI5OTZ9.CRXP1A7WOeoJeXxjNni43kdQwgnWNReilDMblYTn_I0

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# EAS project ID (build-time only)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Run `eas init` once locally — it registers the app on expo.dev and prints a
# UUID. Set that UUID here and as the EAS_PROJECT_ID GitHub Actions secret so
# CI can link builds to the right EAS project without an interactive prompt.
# EAS_PROJECT_ID=xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Sentry crash reporting (optional)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Leave this UNSET for local dev / Expo Go — the Sentry SDK stays dormant and
# nothing is sent. Set it only on production web/native builds so crashes and
# handled errors (cutout upload, editor persistence, page export) are reported.
# Get the DSN from: Sentry -> Project Settings -> Client Keys (DSN). It's a
# public value, safe to inline in the client bundle.
#   * Vercel (web):  add EXPO_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN under Environment Variables
#   * EAS (native):  add it to the `eas.json` build profile `env`, or as a secret
# EXPO_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=https://<key>@<org>.ingest.sentry.io/<project>

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Sentry source-map upload (build-time only — NOT EXPO_PUBLIC_)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These are read by the Sentry Metro/Expo plugin during a production build to
# upload source maps, so minified web/native stack frames become readable in the
# dashboard. They are NOT inlined into the bundle — keep SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN
# secret (Vercel/EAS/GitHub Actions secrets, never committed). Source maps still
# build without them; the upload step is simply skipped.
# SENTRY_ORG=scrappd
# SENTRY_PROJECT=scrappd-mobile
# SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN=<org auth token with project:releases scope>
